The paper is about comparing the retrieval effectiveness of different web search engines, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The study also takes into account the results descriptions, which could be related to Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Deep Learning (cs.DL). The practical implications of the study could be relevant to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as well.
